   <body>
      <section>
         <sectiondiv>
            <p>In a system where the units work in parallel,
the parallel communication shares the operation mode of each unit
with the other units. The behavior of a redundant system will be different
depending on if the system have individual batteries or a common battery.</p>
            <note type="important">Depending on parameter settings for your specific
system design, the tables might not show all system behaviors or your
system might behave differently in a certain situation.</note>
            <note>The shown behaviors assume that boost charge is not inhibited.</note>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section>
         <title>Redundant System with Individual Batteries</title>
         <sectiondiv>
            <p>In a redundant system with individual batteries the
parallel communication is used to share the operation mode and load
status between the units. This will determine the operation mode of
each unit in the system.</p>
